&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The James Paget University Hospitals Critical Care Services (ITU/HDU) Sister, Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: Full Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type: One Permanent&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a permanent Band 6 nurse role within the Critical Care Team (ICU/HDU) at the James Paget University Hospital. We are a 12 bedded ICU/HDU and operate a 12 hour shift system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The posts would offer the successful candidate excellent personal development opportunities in management and leadership. The positions would be ideal for someone who is committed to critical care nursing and the delivery of high quality care to the critically ill patient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have recent Band 6 experience in ICU or experience in ICU with shift co-ordination in the absence of a sister/charge nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be a proactive, willing and motivated individual. A commitment to Critical Care nursing as well as your own personal and professional development will be essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date will be confirmed later.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details and to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Senior Sister Sue Bird, Senior Sister Jo Larter Senior Sister Julie North Senior Sister Priya Mathew on 01493 452277.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
